# C++ Conformance (MSVC v145)

The project compiles with `/std:c++latest` and `/WX` (warnings as errors). Be aware of these strict conformance requirements.

## Concepts: Type Requirements Need `typename`

In a `requires` expression, checking for a nested type must use `typename`:

```cpp
// WRONG — MSVC treats this as an expression, not a type requirement
concept Foo = requires(T t) { T::SomeType; };

// CORRECT
concept Foo = requires(T t) { typename T::SomeType; };
```

## C++20 Operator Rewriting

Do NOT define both `operator==` and `operator!=` as members. C++20 auto-synthesizes `!=` from `==`. Having both causes C7692 ambiguity errors. Always make `operator==` const:

```cpp
// WRONG
bool operator==(const Foo& o) { return ...; }
bool operator!=(const Foo& o) { return !(*this == o); }

// CORRECT — C++20 synthesizes operator!= automatically
bool operator==(const Foo& o) const { return ...; }
```

## User-Defined Literal Operators

No space between `""` and the suffix (C++23 deprecation, C5311):

```cpp
// WRONG
constexpr Foo operator"" _bar(uint64_t v) noexcept;

// CORRECT
constexpr Foo operator""_bar(uint64_t v) noexcept;
```

## Eigen / NanoGUI Deprecation Warnings

NanoGUI's bundled Eigen uses deprecated `std::float_denorm_style`. This is silenced in `pch.h`:

```cpp
#define _SILENCE_CXX23_DENORM_DEPRECATION_WARNING
```

Do not remove this define — it will break the build.
